              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP",
                "SCIN",
                "PPAC",
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The scintillator was constructed",
                "at the NSCL using a 300x150x0.3 mm3 pressed sheet of",
                "UPS-923A (BC-400 equivalent) plastic, manufactured by",
                "Scintillation Technologies (Shirley, MA). The",
                "trajectory of reaction residues in both the dispersive",
                " (orthogonal to the magnetic dipole field) and",
                "nondispersive directions was measured using two",
                "position-sensitive cathode readout drift chambers",
                " (CRDC) placed either side of the scintillator.",
                "Energy-loss measurements were performed using a",
                "16-channel segmented ion chamber filled with C3F8 gas",
                "operated between 340-400 Torr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was constructed from a 20x20 mm2 piece of",
                "electronic grade polycrystalline diamond,",
                "manufactured by Element Six (Cambridge, MA), with a",
                "nominal thickness of 100 mu-m (35 mg/cm2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Reaction residues were identified at the",
                "focal plane of the spectrograph via time-of-flight",
                "and energy-loss measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The fission fragment yield per incident beam particle",
                "was determined in each rigidity setting as Y (A,Z,q)",
                "= N(A,Z,q)/(Sf*NFP*f1*f2*f3), where N(A,Z,q) is the",
                "number of ions extracted for a given charge state",
                "from the fitted A/q data, NFP is the total number of",
                "triggers registered by the focal-plane scintillator,",
                "and Sf is a scale factor relating the focal-plane",
                "triggers to the beam-on-target current, q is charge",
                "state, and f1,f2, f3 correction factors. The fission",
                "fragment yield is related to the cross section as",
                "sigma(A,Z,q) = Y(A,A,q)/(nt*epsilon(A,Z,q)*psi(Z,q)),",
                "where where epsilon(A,Z,q) is the ion transmission",
                "through the spectrometer, psi(Z,q) is the charge-state",
                "production probability, and nt is the number of target",
                "atoms per square centimeter (1.68*10**21 cm-2)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Using the LISE code, the transmission of",
                "all isotopes for the main configuration was calculated.",
                "Then, 10 calculations, varying one of the five",
                "parameters at their minimum and maximum values. were",
                "performed. The deviations from the main configuration's",
                "transmission provide the transmission uncertainties,",
                "which are presented. The yield errors are based on a",
                "chi-squared analysis of Gaussian fits."
              ]
            }
          ],
